{#- §04 CREDENTIALS (checks-list in incl-card) — white -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="s2q-credentials">
  <div class="ct read">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§04</span><span class="idx__t">Certified by Intuit</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:24ch;margin-bottom:12px;">Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor credentials</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:60ch;">Migrating off Sage means building the QuickBooks destination correctly &mdash; the right chart of accounts mapped from your nominal codes, lists, and structure from day one. Every TechBrot operator holds active Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor credentials across the full QuickBooks stack, plus the Intuit Certified Bookkeeping Professional credential. Verification available on request.</p>
    <div class="incl-card">
      <h3>Active credentials, every operator</h3>
      <ul class="checklist">{%- for c in credentials %}<li>{{ c | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}</ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- §05 PRODUCTS (which Sage — 4 buyer cards → lift) — sand -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="s2q-products" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§05</span><span class="idx__t">Which Sage are you leaving</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:22ch;margin-bottom:12px;">Sage is a family &mdash; the move depends on which.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 36px;max-width:60ch;">Each Sage product stores data differently, so each migration is mapped to its specifics. Identifying your exact Sage product is the first step we take &mdash; and it changes the scope, the path, and sometimes the recommendation itself.</p>
    <div class="r-2">
      {%- for s in products %}
      <div class="lift"><span class="lift__n">{% if loop.index < 10 %}0{% endif %}{{ loop.index }}</span><div><h3>{{ s.opener | safe }}</h3><p>{{ s.body | safe }}</p></div></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- §06 COVERAGE (6 numbered deliverables → deliver--3 lattice) — white -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="s2q-coverage">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§06</span><span class="idx__t">What the migration covers</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:20ch;margin-bottom:12px;">A clean arrival, not a raw import.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 36px;max-width:60ch;">The difference between a Sage migration and a data dump is the mapping and verification below &mdash; the work that makes the QuickBooks file trustworthy on day one and ties it back to your Sage numbers.</p>
    <div class="deliver deliver--3">
      {%- for d in coverage %}
      <div class="deliver__cell">
        <span class="lift__n" aria-hidden="true">{{ d.num }}</span>
        <h3>{{ d.name | safe }}</h3>{% if d.body %}<p>{{ d.body | safe }}</p>{% endif %}
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- §07 TRANSFERS (3 honest buckets → lift cards) — sand -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="s2q-transfers" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§07</span><span class="idx__t">What transfers vs. what rebuilds</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:20ch;margin-bottom:12px;">Honest about what comes across.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 36px;max-width:60ch;">No migration carries everything. Knowing what transfers, what rebuilds, and what stays archived in Sage is half of doing it right &mdash; and it&rsquo;s what we settle in the scope before any work begins.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for h in transfers %}
      <div class="lift"><span class="lift__n">{% if loop.index < 10 %}0{% endif %}{{ loop.index }}</span><div><h3>{{ h.opener | safe }}</h3><p>{{ h.body | safe }}</p></div></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- §08 PHASES (4-phase HowTo → process-grid) — white -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="s2q-phases">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§08</span><span class="idx__t">How the Sage migration works</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:18ch;margin-bottom:12px;">From your Sage file to a verified QuickBooks file.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 44px;max-width:60ch;">Every Sage-to-QuickBooks migration follows the same four-phase sequence &mdash; with the conversion verified against your Sage trial balance built in.</p>
    <div class="process-grid">
      {%- for s in phases %}
      <div class="process-step"><div class="process-step__n{% if loop.last %} process-step__n--done{% endif %}">PHASE {{ s.num }}{% if loop.last %} &check;{% endif %}</div>{% if s.name %}<h3>{{ s.name | safe }}</h3>{% endif %}<p>{{ s.body | safe }}</p>{% if s.when %}<p style="margin-top:8px;"><strong>{{ s.when | safe }}</strong></p>{% endif %}</div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

